records.addlTxt:
Defendant Thomas Daniel Urbaniak in court with attorney Lynn Ellen Hackbarth.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to NO CONTEST.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 months in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 year.
Conditions:  
*  Referred to the Mental Health Unit of the probation department;
*  Take all prescribed medications;
*  No contact with the victim, Lashawanda A.;
*  Letter of apologfy to Lashawanda A.;
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed necessary;
*  Absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Mental health evaluation/treatment deemed necessary;
*  Pay costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
